               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_liturg_e_37-item1" n="1" class="#liturgica">
						               <title type="desc" key="work_10649">Breviary of Chertsey Abbey</title>
                      
                     <note>(part)</note>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_liturg_e_37-item1-item1">
                        <locus>(fol.3)</locus>
                        <title>Temporale from Sunday after the octave of the Epiphany to the end.</title> 
                        <note>Preceding it are two leaves from the sanctorale for St. Peter's chains 
                     (fol.1)
                      and St. James the Apostle 
                     (fol.2)</note>
                        <note>Other parts of the same MS. are MSS. Lat. liturg d. 42, e. 6 (Summary Catalogue, no. 32558), and e. 39.  An 18th cent. foliation which presumably went through the whole volume has been almost totally erased, but the present fol.52 was 69 in this foliation, and fol.93 = 110. The leaves in MS. Lat. liturg. e.6 were numbered 221–5, 306–8, 34[-].</note>
                     </msItem>
                     
                     
                     
                     
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="perg">
                        <support>parchment</support>
                       
                        <extent>iii (modern parchment) + 156 + iii (modern parchment) <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
