                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>Fine miniature, borders, historiated and other initials. By the
                        <persName role="artist" key="person_31911557">Master of the Queen Mary Psalter</persName> and his workshop. (P&amp;A iii. 543, pl.
            LIV)
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote>Historiated initial on a ground of gold and blue (fol.1) showing the angel releasing St. Peter, with partial border, smaller gold initials on blue and rose grounds, and many small blue and gold flourished initials</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>On fol.154v and 155v a later hand added the prayers <hi rend="italic">Ante conspectum dominice maiestatis</hi>, and <hi rend="italic">Si tantum reatum</hi>, with the Nicene creed.</additions>
